bug.short_desc: Save Dialog (Animation): Can't read the dialog text , when the dialog is opened a second time.

long_desc.thetext:
Can't read the dialog text , when the dialog is opened a second time.
It works perfect, when I open the dialog the first time, but when I open it a second time, then I can't read the text from the dialog.
See screen shot for more details.

This issue looks like an IE rendering bug. If you look carefully, you can see that the text which has had a black color, now seems to be transparent. It looks like the text is an alpha channel for the widget. Pretty cool, I did not know IE was capable of such rendering techniques. However, I am not sure how to fix this within the qx.fx namespace...
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
